---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Is ZVault really free?',
    a: 'Yes. The CLI, local vault, all engines (KV, Transit, PKI), web dashboard, and Shamir seal are free forever under MIT. No credit card, no account needed. You only pay if you want cloud vault + AI Mode.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I use ZVault in production?',
    a: 'Yes. With ZVault Cloud (Pro+), you manage secrets per environment (dev/staging/prod) from one dashboard. Your app fetches secrets at runtime via SDK or CLI using service tokens. No AWS Secrets Manager needed.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Does this replace AWS Secrets Manager?',
    a: 'For most teams, yes. ZVault Cloud gives you multi-environment secrets, service tokens for CI/CD and production, runtime SDKs (Node, Go, Python), and AI integration — all for $8/dev/mo flat instead of $0.40/secret/mo.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is AI Mode?',
    a: 'AI Mode includes the MCP server that connects to your IDE\'s AI assistant (Cursor, Kiro, Continue). It lets AI see what secrets exist without seeing values, using zvault:// references instead of raw .env files.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Where are my secrets stored?',
    a: 'Free tier: on your machine, encrypted with AES-256-GCM. Cloud tier: encrypted in ZVault Cloud (AES-256-GCM, per-org encryption keys). Your secrets are always encrypted at rest — we never store plaintext.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What happens if ZVault Cloud goes down?',
    a: 'SDKs cache secrets in memory at boot, so your running apps continue working. For new deployments, we maintain 99.9% uptime SLA (Team+) with multi-region infrastructure.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I self-host for free?',
    a: 'Absolutely. Self-host the vault, CLI, and dashboard for free. Cloud features (environments, service tokens, SDKs, AI Mode) require a Pro license key, validated locally via Ed25519 signatures — no phone-home.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What does "per developer" mean?',
    a: 'A "developer" is anyone who uses cloud vault or AI Mode. Service tokens for CI/CD and production don\'t count as seats.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How is this different from HashiCorp Vault?',
    a: 'HashiCorp Vault requires significant setup and operational overhead. ZVault installs in 2 minutes, imports your .env, has native AI integration, and includes a cloud platform — all MIT licensed, not BSL.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What if I cancel?',
    a: 'Your local vault and secrets remain intact. Cloud secrets can be exported before cancellation. The local vault is always free and open source.',
  },
];
---

<section class="py-24" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <p class="text-muted text-lg">Everything you need to know.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto space-y-2">
      {faqs.map((faq, i) => (
        <details class="group bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl overflow-hidden" open={i < 2}>
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none text-sm font-medium hover:bg-bg-card-hover transition-colors">
            {faq.q}
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-dim flex-shrink-0 ml-4 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-[135deg]" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M8 3v10M3 8h10"/>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
            {faq.a}
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
